<topic id='business_definition_secure_children_s_home.description'>
  <title>Description</title>
  <titlealts>
    <searchtitle>NHS Business Definition: Secure Children's Home - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>
  <div>
      <p>
A 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_secure_children_s_home">Secure Children's Home</xref>
 is a 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_justice_organisation">Justice Organisation</xref>.        </p>
      <p>
A 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_secure_children_s_home">Secure Children's Home</xref>
 is a type of 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_youth_detention_accommodation">Youth Detention Accommodation</xref>
 and/or 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_secure_welfare_accommodation">Secure Welfare Accommodation</xref>
 that accommodates children and young people between the ages of 10-17.        </p>
      <p>
A 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_secure_children_s_home">Secure Children's Home</xref>
 is a 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_children_s_home">Children's Home</xref>
 which provides a locked environment and restricts a young person's liberty.        </p>
      <p>
         <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_secure_children_s_home">Secure Children's Homes</xref>:        </p>
      <ul>
         <li>
            <div>
               <p>
provide care and accommodation to children and young people who have been detained or sentenced by the 
                                <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                        keyref="business_definition_youth_justice_board">Youth Justice Board</xref>
 (<xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                        keyref="business_definition_youth_justice_board">YJB</xref>) and those who have been remanded to secure 
                                <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                        keyref="business_definition_local_authority">Local Authority</xref>
 (<xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                        keyref="business_definition_local_authority">LA</xref>) accommodation                    </p>
            </div>
         </li>
         <li>
            <div>
               <p>
also accommodate and care for children and young people who have been placed there on welfare grounds by 
                                <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                        keyref="business_definition_local_authority">Local Authorities</xref>
 and 
                                <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_court">Courts</xref>.                    </p>
            </div>
         </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
For further information on Health and Justice healthcare, see the 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_nhs_england">NHS England</xref>
 website at: 
              <xref href="https://www.england.nhs.uk/commissioning/health-just/"
               scope="external"
               format="html">Health and Justice</xref>.        </p>
  </div>
